GŒ¥ space
A GŒ¥ space is a topological space in which every closed set is a GŒ¥ set. A normal space that is also a GŒ¥ space is called perfectly normal.  For example, every metrizable space is perfectly normal.

See also
FœÉ set, the dual concept; contrast the "G" from German Gebiet 'open set' and "F" from French ferm√© 'closed'.
P-space, any space having the property that every GŒ¥ set is open

